Title: Privilege Escalation: Low Privilege User Can Modify Super Admin-Restricted Employer Data
Description: A low privilege user can not only view but also modify sensitive employer data that is strictly reserved for Super Admins. Due to insufficient access control mechanisms, the user is able to make unauthorized updates to employer details, potentially altering critical business information. This vulnerability poses a serious threat to data integrity and can lead to business disruptions or data manipulation.

Impact:

Unauthorized users can modify sensitive employer data.
Risk of data integrity loss, as business-critical information may be altered by unauthorized users.
Potential for malicious data manipulation, which could lead to operational or financial consequences.
Recommendation:

Implement robust role-based access control (RBAC) to ensure that only authorized users (Super Admins) can update employer data.
Perform thorough server-side validation of user permissions before allowing any data modification.
Conduct regular security audits and testing to ensure that sensitive features are protected from unauthorized access.
